			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Position Description:</p>
<p>
	The director of marketing for Vitrue will be responsible for the development and execution of all strategic marketing plans to grow the brand. This will include social media and corporate communications, supporting sales and partners. Responsibilities will include the following:</p>
<p>
	&bull; Ability to translate business objectives and revenue plans into actionable marketing plans.<br />
	&bull; Design and implement an annual marketing planning process and support/facilitate the development and implementation of marketing plans on a quarterly basis.<br />
	&bull; Provide to the marketing budget input and manage the ongoing expense management.<br />
	&bull; Organize and implement client relation&rsquo;s special events, surveys, activities, or training.<br />
	&bull; Support inside and outside sales efforts including marketing collateral, case studies.<br />
	&bull; Participate in the development of a customer database, and manage the customer contact strategy for various sales and marketing outreach.<br />
	&bull; Oversee and manage the digital marketing aspects of Vitrue&rsquo;s brand including the web site, video, online and search advertising and Facebook presence.<br />
	&bull; Supervise members of the marketing team; assist in defining and hiring additional members of the marketing team.<br />
	Skills</p>
<p>
	Skills</p>
<p>
	&bull; Excellent communication skills, i.e. written and verbal, to develop a wide-range of materials<br />
	&bull; Strong presentation skills including presentation development and communication to small or large audiences or clients<br />
	&bull; Ability to manage and lead direct or indirect colleagues<br />
	&bull; Highly interested and active user/consumer of social media<br />
	&bull; Experienced managing contractors, agencies or other service partners<br />
	&bull; Highly organized and prepared</p>
<p>
	Requirements</p>
<p>
	&bull; College degree with a concentration in marketing, business or communications preferred.<br />
	&bull; At least 3-5 years experience as a marketing director within a professional services, technology or B2B environment.<br />
	&bull; Experience digital marketer who has demonstrated social media experience<br />
	&bull; Must be a self-starter that thrives in a fast-paced environment and able to work w/ all levels in the organization.<br />
	&bull; Ability to lead others and possess consensus-building skills<br />
	&bull; Highly polished presentation and interpersonal skills</p>
<p>
	Compensation &amp; Benefits:</p>
<p>
	&bull; Competitive salary<br />
	&bull; Excellent medical, dental, and life insurance<br />
	&bull; Stock options<br />
	&bull; Great work environment and team<br />
	&bull; Generous vacation time<br />
	&bull; Commission plan<br />
	&bull; Free snacks &amp; drinks<br />
	&bull; Happy Hours<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
